# Velocity Platform

Acceleration layer for AI coding assistants. Provides skills, agents, guardrails, adapters, and organizational knowledge — purely prompt-driven, no CLI or server.

## Domain language

Before feature work: read .velocity/artifacts/context/CONTEXT.md
All names (variables, files, API terms) must match CONTEXT.md glossary.

## Standards

- Engineering: .velocity/project-context/engineering.md
- Testing: .velocity/project-context/testing.md
- Security: .velocity/project-context/security.md

## ADRs

Before designing: read .velocity/knowledge-base/adrs/index.md

## Skills

/grill-with-docs — before feature work; reads CONTEXT.md
/domain-model — align plan to CONTEXT.md before PRD
/to-prd — after grill session
/to-features — PRD → vertical slice board
/to-tasks — features → tasks with blocking relationships
/tdd — per task, fresh window
/improve-codebase-architecture — periodic deepening
/handoff — end of each slice
/sync — regenerate assets after stack changes

## Agents

Engineer — implement skills, agents, templates; create PRs
Architect — design skill chains, adapter architecture, ADRs
Researcher — explore CONTEXT.md, knowledge base, prior slices
Reviewer — review PRs, ADRs, skill quality

## Guardrails

Vertical slices only. No horizontal layer PRs.
No secrets in skill files. Schema version bumps need approval.
Tracer bullet required before expanding any new capability.

## Stack

Markdown + YAML frontmatter, JSON Schema, prompt-driven architecture.
Skills: skills/\*_/SKILL.md — Agents: agents/_.md — Templates: templates/
Schemas: schemas/\*.json — Dogfooding: .velocity/

## Session start

Check .velocity/project-intelligence/stack.md detected_at.
If over 7 days old: run /sync before any feature work.
